04:37.393 --> 04:38.859
Oh.

04:38.861 --> 04:40.861
I'll say something.

04:40.863 --> 04:43.271
No. You've had a whole
lifetime of this. Let me.

04:43.296 --> 04:43.932
Oh.

04:43.933 --> 04:45.483
Barney, are you thinking

04:45.485 --> 04:48.069
you can get your mother
and me back together?

04:48.071 --> 04:49.787
Because I'm married.

04:49.789 --> 04:51.622
My wife is right upstairs!

04:51.624 --> 04:52.657
No, she's not.

04:52.659 --> 04:54.274
What's that?
Nothing!

04:54.276 --> 04:55.710
I'm just trying
to keep you refreshed

04:55.712 --> 04:59.213
through this unexpected and
flukish elevator malfunction!

04:59.215 --> 05:02.616
Here's some water!

05:02.618 --> 05:04.802
Ah... drat.

05:04.804 --> 05:06.304
Clumsy hands much, Barney?

05:06.306 --> 05:08.422
Just disrobe
and send up those wet clothes.

05:08.424 --> 05:11.125
You'll be cold, so I'll send
down strawberry warming gel

05:11.127 --> 05:13.961
and some cozy, zippered masks.

05:13.963 --> 05:16.063
(sighs):
Ooh.

05:16.065 --> 05:18.482
(gasps)
My calligraphy ink!

05:19.818 --> 05:21.468
I mean, the Gretzky photo!

05:23.171 --> 05:25.606
Some bastard
snuck into my room

05:25.608 --> 05:27.525
and spilled ink
all over the Gretzky photo

05:27.527 --> 05:28.909
I was holding for Barney.

05:28.911 --> 05:30.578
Detective Mosby is on the case.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.997
Oh, God, that's horrible.
I know.

05:32.999 --> 05:34.148
It was a gift for Robin.

05:34.150 --> 05:35.783
No, I mean,

05:35.785 --> 05:38.669
"Oh, God, that's horrible.
Detective Mosby's the worst."

05:38.671 --> 05:40.154
Mm, Detective Mosby is

05:40.156 --> 05:41.872
the case-crackingest
private dick on the scene.

05:41.874 --> 05:44.375
Really? Like that case
from eight years ago

05:44.377 --> 05:46.093
you still haven't cracked?

05:46.095 --> 05:47.795
I'm callin' it.

05:50.849 --> 05:52.500
Damn it!

05:52.502 --> 05:54.385
My greatest failure.

05:54.387 --> 05:56.020
I will solve this case.

05:56.022 --> 05:57.521
Now, there were
three people nearby

05:57.523 --> 05:59.190
when Barney gave me
that head shot:

05:59.192 --> 06:02.610
Karate Kid <i>bad boy Billy Zabka,</i>

06:02.612 --> 06:06.013
<i>a shifty-eyed bellhop,</i>

06:06.015 --> 06:08.348
<i>and Robin's cousin Claude</i>
<i>from Quebec</i>

06:08.350 --> 06:10.317
<i>with the neck trouble.</i>

06:10.319 --> 06:13.687
Right, 'cause an elaborate
conspiracy is much more likely

06:13.689 --> 06:17.041
than you leaving the photo
next to an open ink bottle.

06:17.043 --> 06:20.194
Thank you!
You can't even detect sarcasm!

06:20.196 --> 06:22.463
Why don't you just
try to fix the photo?

06:22.465 --> 06:23.714
Don't you have ink remover?

06:23.716 --> 06:24.999
Of course I have ink remover.

06:25.001 --> 06:26.867
I'm not one of those sloppy,
punk calligraphers

06:26.869 --> 06:28.386
who's in it
for glory over craft.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.304
No, we got to solve this!

06:30.306 --> 06:31.839
Now, the question is,

06:31.841 --> 06:34.892
which of those three suspects
had the most cause to frame me?

06:34.894 --> 06:39.213
<i>The one that I replaced</i>
<i>as Barney's best man?</i>

06:39.215 --> 06:41.899
I'm coming for you, Mosby.

06:41.901 --> 06:43.934
Billy Zabka!

06:43.936 --> 06:46.720
Okay, real quick,
I need fresh-cut

06:46.722 --> 06:49.240
English lavender, a copy of
Shakespeare's 18th sonnet,

06:49.242 --> 06:51.826
and enough Nutella
to cover a 60-year-old woman.

06:53.011 --> 06:55.029
Oh, great. You guys escaped.

06:55.031 --> 06:56.363
Got rescued!

06:56.365 --> 06:57.698
Are you okay?

06:57.700 --> 06:59.033
A bit shaken up.

06:59.035 --> 07:00.901
Being trapped
in an elevator is scary.

07:00.903 --> 07:02.837
No, Barney lowered in a TV

07:02.839 --> 07:06.257
showing some pretty
graphic 1970s pornography.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.459
Still, a lot
of familiar faces in there.

07:08.461 --> 07:09.927
Well, not just faces.

07:09.929 --> 07:12.129
I'm gonna go
find my wife.

07:13.381 --> 07:16.250
(sighs)
Nice job, bro.

07:16.252 --> 07:18.919
Mom was just about
to get some action

07:18.921 --> 07:20.554
for the first time
since she conceived me.

07:20.556 --> 07:21.922
Barney, this has to stop.

07:21.924 --> 07:23.107
You're being delusional.

07:23.109 --> 07:24.325
Mom is not getting back
together with Jerry.

07:24.350 --> 07:25.260
(sighs)

07:25.261 --> 07:27.928
Because she's getting back
together with my daddy!

07:32.639 --> 07:34.913
I see what you're doing.

07:34.914 --> 07:37.064
You didn't bring your dad here
to marry us.

07:37.066 --> 07:39.116
You want him to get back
together with Mom!

07:39.118 --> 07:41.519
Which is completely insane,
by the way.

07:41.521 --> 07:43.988
Um, my dad's single,
Mom's single.

07:43.990 --> 07:45.956
Your dad's happily married
with two kids.

07:45.958 --> 07:47.291
Which one makes more sense?

07:47.293 --> 07:48.859
I agree. It's a tie.

07:48.861 --> 07:50.044
What do we do?

07:50.046 --> 07:51.178
You back down

07:51.180 --> 07:52.763
and let me get my mom
and dad back together?

07:52.765 --> 07:54.265
Um, how about <i>you</i> back down

07:54.267 --> 07:56.384
and let me get <i>my</i> mom and dad
back together?

07:56.386 --> 07:58.519
(scoffs)
I can already picture it.

07:58.521 --> 08:00.688
(peppy music plays)

08:00.690 --> 08:04.275
♪ We're reunited
and we're going so strong ♪

08:04.277 --> 08:08.012
