when I ran in to help.

11:17.753 --> 11:19.786
You really expect me
to believe that?

11:19.788 --> 11:22.790
Story checks out.

11:22.792 --> 11:24.725
Sorry, Claude.

11:24.727 --> 11:27.261
<i>De rien.</i>

11:27.263 --> 11:29.013
I don't get it.

11:29.015 --> 11:29.980
We were bonding.

11:30.932 --> 11:34.435
I can't think of
anything I did wrong!

11:34.437 --> 11:36.303
Okay, I did a few things wrong.

11:36.305 --> 11:37.688
For the last time,

11:37.690 --> 11:41.808
I did not leave the bag of
oranges you bought on the roof!

11:44.145 --> 11:46.780
No more breaking the
speed limit. And, uh,

11:46.782 --> 11:50.367
thanks for flagging me down and
telling me she was going 67.

11:50.369 --> 11:52.202
Just following the rules,
Officer.

11:52.204 --> 11:55.489
Oh. She's also not
wearing her seat belt.

11:57.926 --> 12:00.010
You are not allowed
to use that word!

12:00.012 --> 12:02.263
Only <i>we're</i> allowed
to use that word!

12:02.265 --> 12:04.632
I am so sorry.

12:04.634 --> 12:05.516
I will never

12:05.518 --> 12:08.135
call you or anyone else a...

12:08.137 --> 12:10.054
Trekkie again.

12:10.056 --> 12:12.556
But I apologized
and you accepted.

12:12.558 --> 12:14.858
I even bought you more oranges.

12:19.531 --> 12:22.349
Look, it wasn't you, okay?

12:22.351 --> 12:25.719
Baby, I know your speech
at the Model U.N. is a big deal,

12:25.721 --> 12:28.205
but I'm just not sure
I'll make it in time.

12:28.207 --> 12:29.623
I'm trying.

12:29.625 --> 12:30.824
You know what?

12:30.826 --> 12:32.543
Don't bother coming.

12:36.331 --> 12:38.499
So, back at the airport,
that story was true?

12:38.501 --> 12:39.533
You have a daughter?

12:39.535 --> 12:41.251
She lives with her dad.

12:41.253 --> 12:44.705
And since I travel for work,
I miss a lot of stuff.

12:45.757 --> 12:49.009
I only work as hard as I do
to provide for her.

12:49.011 --> 12:52.346
But kids,
they don't understand logic.

12:52.348 --> 12:54.815
Kids understand who shows up.

12:54.817 --> 12:56.183
That's why

12:56.185 --> 12:57.818
her dad's her hero...

12:57.820 --> 13:01.572
and I get hung up on.

13:01.574 --> 13:03.073
Go see your daughter's speech.

13:03.075 --> 13:05.159
If you show up,
all will be forgiven.

13:05.161 --> 13:06.410
Just drop it.

13:07.028 --> 13:08.362
And drop me at home.

13:08.364 --> 13:09.947
Then head out to your wedding.

13:09.949 --> 13:11.582
End of discussion.

13:13.401 --> 13:15.252
Barney,
even if your plan worked,

13:15.254 --> 13:16.920
you'd be destroying
your dad's marriage.

13:16.922 --> 13:19.072
Okay, you may have a point.

13:19.074 --> 13:20.207
Can I suggest something?

13:20.209 --> 13:20.907
(sighs)

13:20.909 --> 13:21.925
Truce?

13:21.927 --> 13:23.910
We both agree to drop this.

13:23.912 --> 13:25.912
Agreed.

13:25.914 --> 13:27.364
Hey, I got a replacement bottle

13:27.366 --> 13:30.184
of 30-year Glen McKenna.
Okay.

13:30.186 --> 13:32.553
Look, even if Mom
never gets back together

13:32.555 --> 13:35.305
with either one of our dads,
we're still brothers.

13:35.307 --> 13:37.274
It's not a competition.

13:37.276 --> 13:39.560
(chuckles)

13:41.946 --> 13:43.113
I win!

13:43.115 --> 13:45.282
Hoo-hoo!

13:47.435 --> 13:49.657
Get your damn
hands off my mom!

13:49.658 --> 13:51.375
Get your damn hands
on my mom!

13:51.377 --> 13:52.709
One on, one off?

13:52.711 --> 13:54.845
What the hell is
going on here?

13:54.847 --> 13:56.980
After you boys tracked Sam down
a few years back,

13:56.982 --> 13:58.949
we got in touch.
We became friends again,

13:58.951 --> 14:00.984
started hanging out.
And then one day,

14:00.986 --> 14:03.420
she went from being
Loretta to being...

14:03.422 --> 14:05.555
Lo-ret-ta.
(chuckles)

14:05.557 --> 14:06.974
We wanted to wait
to tell you

14:06.976 --> 14:08.191
because it's still new,

14:08.193 --> 14:10.060
but it was inevitable
you'd find out

14:10.062 --> 14:12.396
once Sam came
to perform the ceremony.

14:12.398 --> 14:13.847
Is that what you
two call it?

14:13.849 --> 14:16.233
"Performing
the ceremony"?

14:16.235 --> 14:17.484
Oh, Sam's marrying you
tomorrow, dear.

14:17.486 --> 14:20.020
Right. Thank you, Reverend.
Look,

14:20.022 --> 14:22.539
is there any way you guys
can be all right with this?

14:22.541 --> 14:24.741
Of course I am!
(clears throat)

14:24.743 --> 14:27.377
Barney?

14:27.379 --> 14:30.330
I know I've been acting crazy
today, but...

14:30.332 --> 14:32.549
I just have
one real question, Mom,

14:32.551 --> 14:34.367
and I want an honest answer.

14:35.136 --> 14:36.136
Is there a scenario--

14:36.138 --> 14:37.170
and hear me out--

14:37.172 --> 14:39.339
where you might consider

14:39.341 --> 14:41.875
doing kind of a three-way deal
with both of our dads?

14:41.877 --> 14:44.061
God! What is wrong with you?!
Oh, dude, come on!

14:44.063 --> 14:46.313
(sobs)
That's what I thought!

14:48.766 --> 14:51.018
It's time to
admit it, Ted.

14:51.020 --> 14:53.654
You spilled the ink.
There's no conspiracy.

14:53.656 --> 14:55.022
I guess you're right.

14:55.024 --> 14:56.440
I mean, the only other person

14:56.442 --> 14:58.742
who saw Barney give me
that photo...

14:58.744 --> 14:59.993
was you.

14:59.995 --> 15:01.745
(dramatic sting)

15:01.747 --> 15:03.063
Hey. Idiot.

15:03.065 --> 15:04.731
While you've been

15:04.733 --> 15:07.117
playing detective,
I've been cleaning up your mess.

15:07.119 --> 15:10.236
Look, the ink remover works.

15:10.238 --> 15:11.004
I'm gonna
finish this.

15:11.006 --> 15:13.090
You come clean to Barney.

15:13.092 --> 15:14.574
(sighs):
Okay.

15:14.576 --> 15:16.626
She's been
missing all day,

15:16.628 --> 15:20.881
a-and I found what appears to be
a-a suicide note on my bed.

15:20.883 --> 15:23.350
But it doesn't
really sound like her.

15:23.352 --> 15:27.854
"I'm going to kill my--
wait for it-- self."

15:29.440 --> 15:31.274
Is everything okay
with Mr. Zabka?

15:31.276 --> 15:35.261
Wait. W-Wait. Why do you think
that's Billy Zabka?

15:35.263 --> 15:37.614
(The Beastie Boys'
"Sabotage" begins)

15:37.616 --> 15:39.766
WOMAN:
<i>See?</i>

15:39.768 --> 15:41.735
The man from the
lobby got this massage.

15:41.737 --> 15:43.820
A younger gentleman bought it
for him as a gift.

15:43.822 --> 15:45.238
He even signed his name for him.

15:45.240 --> 15:46.439
Right here.

15:48.000 --> 15:54.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

15:59.453 --> 16:01.304
I'm telling all y'all...

16:01.306 --> 16:03.006
it's Zabka-tage.

16:03.008 --> 16:05.458
♪ I can't stand it,
I know you planned it ♪

16:05.460 --> 16:08.512
♪ I'm gonna set it straight,
this Watergate ♪

16:08.514 --> 16:10.296
♪ I can't stand rocking
when I'm in here ♪

16:10.298 --> 16:12.632
♪ 'Cause your crystal ball
ain't so crystal clear ♪

16:12.634 --> 16:16.302
♪ So while you sit back
and wonder why ♪

16:16.304 --> 16:19.756
♪ I got this ... thorn
in my side ♪

16:19.758 --> 16:21.291
(shouts)

16:21.293 --> 16:23.326
NARRATOR: <i>Lily's second tackle</i>
<i>of the weekend.</i>

16:23.328 --> 16:26.947
♪ Sabotage.

16:26.949 --> 16:28.915
Wakey, wakey.

16:32.820 --> 16:34.237
DAPHNE:
Wait, this isn't...

16:34.239 --> 16:35.589
It's your
daughter's school.

16:35.591 --> 16:37.174
You need to go in.

16:37.176 --> 16:39.159
She asked me not to come,
Marshall.

16:39.161 --> 16:41.545
This doesn't make any sense.

16:41.547 --> 16:43.346
Kids don't understand logic.

16:43.348 --> 16:46.550
Kids understand who shows up.

17:05.536 --> 17:08.622
People say
children are the future.

17:08.624 --> 17:10.190
I say...

17:10.192 --> 17:11.657
oil is the future!

17:11.660 --> 17:14.044
Don't listen to these
gutless environmental sissies!

17:14.046 --> 17:15.862
That's my baby.
Drill in the oceans!

17:15.864 --> 17:17.497
Thank you.
Drill in the wetlands!

17:17.499 --> 17:19.299
Pumpkin head.
Drill in the national parks!

17:19.300 --> 17:20.532
You're welcome.

17:20.535 --> 17:22.135
Drill, baby, drill!
Drill, baby, drill!

17:22.137 --> 17:24.204
AUDIENCE (chanting): Drill, baby, drill!
We should go.

17:24.205 --> 17:26.506
Drill, baby, drill!
Drill, baby, drill!

17:26.508 --> 17:29.843
Drill, baby, drill!
Drill, baby, drill!

17:29.845 --> 17:31.344
Drill, baby, drill!

17:31.346 --> 17:32.979
You said it was nuts

17:32.981 --> 17:35.215
to think that my mom and dad
would get back together.

17:35.217 --> 17:36.716
But that's what happened
for James.

17:36.718 --> 17:39.069
I've been dreaming of that
since I was five.

17:39.071 --> 17:42.055
Well, that and my own
operational Death Star.

17:42.057 --> 17:44.357
But mostly them
getting back together.

17:44.359 --> 17:46.359
Why does James get it
and I don't?

17:46.361 --> 17:47.444
Well, think about it.

17:47.446 --> 17:49.996
You have me,
your dad has Cheryl...

17:49.998 --> 17:51.081
"So to summarize:

17:51.083 --> 17:52.165
"I'm super dead,

17:52.167 --> 17:54.668
"you should totally bone
Loretta,

17:54.670 --> 17:55.418
"and I never

17:55.420 --> 17:57.254
loved you, Cheryl,"

17:57.256 --> 17:59.923
which is misspelled.

17:59.925 --> 18:01.842
...but James is going
through a divorce.

18:01.844 --> 18:03.743
He just lost his family.

18:03.745 --> 18:06.796
I-I know you've been
dreaming of this, but...

18:06.798 --> 18:09.432
maybe he needs "Mom
and Dad" more than you.

18:10.751 --> 18:14.554
So, Billy, did you really think
you could get away with it?

18:14.556 --> 18:15.605
Actually, I did.

18:15.607 --> 18:16.473
Ah.
I was gonna

18:16.475 --> 18:17.757
give this to Barney

18:17.759 --> 18:18.859
and say I'd driven an hour away

18:18.861 --> 18:20.977
to get a replacement
from an autograph dealer.

18:20.979 --> 18:22.879
<i>First, I needed an alibi.</i>

18:22.881 --> 18:24.781
<i>So I got Barney's dad a massage</i>

18:24.783 --> 18:27.067
<i>but signed in my name.</i>

18:27.069 --> 18:30.436
<i>Then I switched the Gretzky</i>
<i>head shot with one of myself.</i>

18:30.438 --> 18:33.206
<i>I always travel with 2,000</i>
<i>of those handsome devils</i>

18:33.208 --> 18:35.408
<i>in the trunk of my car.</i>

18:36.827 --> 18:39.746
I have so many questions
for you, but first...

18:39.748 --> 18:43.166
you keep 2,000 head shots
of yourself in your trunk?

18:43.168 --> 18:44.968
No one ever wants them!
They only want

18:44.970 --> 18:47.170
the "good guy's" autograph!

18:47.172 --> 18:49.806
In the '80s, I was the bad guy
in every movie.

18:49.808 --> 18:52.425
Do you know what my life
has been like?

18:52.427 --> 18:55.812
<i>Every premiere,</i>
<i>when I came on-screen...</i>

18:55.814 --> 18:56.980
(crowd booing)

18:56.982 --> 18:58.565
<i>I wasn't a bad guy</i>
<i>in real life,</i>

18:58.567 --> 19:00.400
<i>just a kick-ass actor.</i>

19:00.402 --> 19:01.818
<i>No one got that.</i>

19:01.820 --> 19:03.970
<i>It happened everywhere I went.</i>

19:03.972 --> 19:06.606
(crowd booing) <i>Somehow,</i>
<i>people always had popcorn.</i>

19:06.608 --> 19:10.577
<i>25 years of getting</i>
<i>crane-kicked in the nuts,</i>

19:10.579 --> 19:14.447
<i>until Barney Stinson gave me</i>
<i>the best moment of my life.</i>

19:14.449 --> 19:17.083
Hey. Hey, some issues
just came up with Ted, so...

19:17.085 --> 19:18.335
will you be my best man?

19:18.337 --> 19:19.703
Sure.
Thanks.

19:22.623 --> 19:24.791
WOMAN: Hello?
Mom?

19:24.793 --> 19:26.760
(booing)
No, no, listen, listen.

19:26.762 --> 19:29.012
I just became
somebody's best man.

19:29.014 --> 19:32.665
(gasps) You can come
to Thanksgiving this year!

19:32.667 --> 19:35.001
To Barney Stinson,
I wasn't a bad guy.

19:35.003 --> 19:39.339
To Barney Stinson, I was
the best man.

19:39.341 --> 19:43.059
I thought if Ted screwed up
again, I'd have another shot.

19:44.111 --> 19:46.613
But I guess this time
I really was the bad guy.

19:46.615 --> 19:48.281
Hey, Ted,
what's so urgent?

19:48.283 --> 19:50.867
I have something
to tell you.

19:50.869 --> 19:52.152
(sighs)

19:52.154 --> 19:54.687
I destroyed
that Gretzky head shot

19:54.689 --> 19:57.190
and I couldn't fix it.
Billy saved the day

19:57.192 --> 19:59.960
by getting a new one
from an autograph dealer nearby.

19:59.962 --> 20:01.127
A-An hour away.

20:01.129 --> 20:03.163
An hour away. Just be cool.

20:03.165 --> 20:05.131
Awesome. Thanks, Billy!

20:05.133 --> 20:06.466
(chuckles)

20:06.468 --> 20:09.085
Ah.

20:09.087 --> 20:11.054
And, Ted...

20:11.056 --> 20:13.423
I really appreciate
that you told the truth.

20:13.425 --> 20:15.141
Ow...
Psych!

20:15.143 --> 20:16.676
Billy rules,
Ted drools,

20:16.678 --> 20:17.877
Stinson out.

20:19.730 --> 20:21.765
You're all right, Mosby.

20:21.767 --> 20:25.235
NARRATOR: <i>And for an all too rare moment</i>
<i>that weekend,</i>

20:25.237 --> 20:26.719
<i>everything was all right.</i>

20:26.721 --> 20:28.355
(elevator thumps, stops)

